===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|sound}}, {{m|enm|sund}}, {{m|enm|isund}}, {{m|enm|ȝesund}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|sund}}, {{m|ang|ġesund||sound, safe, whole, uninjured, healthy, prosperous}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*gasundaz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*sundaz||healthy}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*sunt-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*swent-||vigorous, active, healthy}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|sound}}, {{m|sco|soun||healthy, sound}}, {{cog|stq|suund}}, {{m|stq|gesuund||healthy}}, {{cog|fy|sûn||healthy}}, {{cog|nl|gezond||healthy, sound}}, {{cog|nds|sund}}, {{m|nds|gesund||healthy}}, {{cog|de|gesund||healthy, sound}}, {{cog|da|sund||healthy}}, {{cog|sv|sund||sound, healthy}}, {{cog|ga|fétaid||to be able}}. Related also to {{cog|nl|gezwind||fast, quick}}, {{cog|de|geschwind||fast, quick}}, {{cog|ang|swīþ||strong, mighty, powerful, active, severe, violent}}. See {{l|en|swith}}.

